50|$|Thomas Rowe Price, Jr. founded T. Rowe Price & Associates in Baltimore in 1937. The {{firm was}} {{originally}} headquartered at 10 Light Street and staffed {{by a small}} pool of associates, many of whom left Legg Mason's precursor, MacKubin, Legg and Co. along with Mr. Price. Initially a very small firm focused on wealth management and private investing accounts for Baltimore-area families, the company struggled through the <b>financial</b> <b>turbulence</b> of the Great Depression and World War II before gaining solid footing {{at the end of}} the 1940s. By 1950, its clientele grew too large for the staff to manage accounts individually, so the firm incorporated and launched its first mutual fund, the T. Rowe Price Growth Stock Fund.|$|E
